[8972, 14513, 9035, 14562].description: Collapse structure—Circular depression characterized by strata dipping inward toward a central point. May reflect collapse of a deep-seated breccia pipe that originated in the Redwall Limestone.

[8938, 14638, 9052, 14687].description: Sinkhole—Circular depression caused by dissolution of gypsum in the Kaibab and Toroweap Formations. Typically smaller in diameter than collapse structures with strata truncated around margin. Sinkholes breached by drainages not shown.
